# Reap idle per-cell test workdirs created by the CI workflows. Each
# cell bind-mounts a unique subdir under /mnt/ci_scratch (host path
# embeds github.run_id + strategy.job-index; see
# .github/workflows/test.yml). Cleanup mechanics: `e` cleans files
# older than the Age field, then recursively removes empty subdirs that
# are also old enough -- so a completed/crashed cell's tree gets eaten
# once its contents are >1d stale. The dataset mount itself stays.
# Age=1d is comfortably beyond the harness's 1500s timeout, so a live
# cell can't be reaped mid-run.
#
# Production runner workdirs (workdir_<inst>) hold per-job artifacts
# split across:
#  - _work/    : actions/checkout's clone cache; reuse across jobs is a
#                real speedup, so we don't reap.
#  - _temp/    : per-job scratch (downloads, decompressed actions).
#                actions/runner stages each job's tool installs and
#                checkouts under here; safe to reap after a week.
#  - _actions/ : downloaded action repos shared across jobs. Reusable
#                but heavy; 30d covers any reasonable cache window.
# Globbed paths match every workdir_<inst> automatically; rules are
# no-ops on hosts that haven't created any workdirs yet.
#
# Age fields are tilde-prefixed (~1d / ~7d / ~30d) so cleanup is
# mtime-based per man 5 tmpfiles.d: without the tilde the rule also
# considers atime, which would silently re-age any file a workflow
# `cat`s (action cache reads, tool installs reading their own
# binaries, etc.), keeping it from ever expiring.
#
# Type Path                                              Mode UID GID Age   Argument
e      /mnt/ci_scratch                                    -    -   -   ~1d
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/workdir_*/_temp        -    -   -   ~7d
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/workdir_*/_actions     -    -   -   ~30d

# actions/runner hardcodes `-v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock`
# on every job container it creates for a workflow's job-level
# `container:` block. The runner asks podman (over the DooD socket
# bind-mounted into the runner container) to create the sibling job
# container and bind-mount /var/run/docker.sock into it. podman is on
# the HOST, so it statfs the path on the host's filesystem -- not
# inside the runner container -- and the create fails with
# "statfs /var/run/docker.sock: no such file or directory" when the
# path is absent on the host. Point /var/run/docker.sock at
# github_runner's rootless podman socket so the host-side statfs
# succeeds AND in-sibling docker CLI calls reach podman's docker-compat
# API. Symlink because /var/run is tmpfs -- systemd-tmpfiles-setup.service
# re-runs this rule at boot. The L rule replaces any pre-existing
# /var/run/docker.sock (man 5 tmpfiles.d), so a stale or differently-
# targeted symlink gets fixed without operator intervention.
L      /var/run/docker.sock                                -    -   -   -    /run/user/{{ github_runner_user.uid }}/podman/podman.sock
